						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and not dated. It refers to a certain <hi rend="bold">Aṇṇiga Dhanañjaya</hi> and a son of <hi rend="bold">Mahēśvara-Sāhaṇi</hi> and records the grant by Aṇṇiga of a <hi rend="italic">kalnāḍu</hi> to a hero with admiration at his recapture of the lifted cattle and a gift of land to a Bhaṭṭāraka (god ?). The characters of the record belong to the 8th or 9th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>First Section.</p>						

